title: Names are opportunities.
pid: 1282d023-f676-46a4-aff9-2a85e6d847a1
body: |2-
  This:
    x = df [ df.a > 0 ]
       . groupby("b")
       . c . mean()                                
  and this:
    positive_margin_orders = orders[orders.margin > 0]
    average_revenue_by_region =
      positive_margin_orders
      . groupby("region")
      . revenue . mean()
  do the same thing.

  Which is easier to understand?
